  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nThe configuration page for the Sync module on the [docs](https://docs.nethermind.io/nethermind/ethereum-client/configuration/sync) shows that the default value for the `AncientBodiesBarrier` and `AncientReceiptsBarrier` flags is 0. This is not exactly correct as the default number depends on the network or nethermind configuration. It would be good if these values are somewhat displayed in a way the user would know if he/she needs to change this value or not depending of the network or configuration.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nClear information about the default values being used for each network or config (at least the major ones) should be displayed. Maybe some instructions on how to look for this value in the `.config` would do the trick.\r\n",
